{
  "id": "class_0044",
  "name": "Plague Lantern Bearer",
  "title_completion": "a Plague Lantern Bearer",
  "flavor_text": "In the Plague City, the lantern-bearers came before the burial carts \u2014 not to guide the living, but to judge them. She holds her light steady over the sick and the sealed doors, and where it falls, the miasma retreats like a tide that knows shame. The brine in the air tastes like penance; she has learned not to mind.",
